claim.claim-text:
1. A transmitting apparatus comprising:
a first symbol generation section that selects one point of a first plurality of signal points as a first symbol, the first plurality of signal points being arranged per unit time on an IQ plane based on a first mapping pattern where a plurality of bits are allocated;
a second symbol generation section that selects one point of a second plurality of signal points as a second symbol, the second plurality of signal points being arranged per unit time on the IQ plane based on a second mapping pattern where different bit allocation from the first mapping pattern is performed;
a first antenna that transmits the first symbol; and
a second antenna that transmits the second symbol in a common frequency and a common transmission time with the first symbol, wherein:
the first symbol is arranged at a first position on the IQ plane where a first bit set in the plurality of bits is allocated;
the first plurality of signal points are divided into four groups based on specific two bits in the plurality of bits;
in each of the groups, the first plurality of signal points are arranged per first distance in a horizontal direction or in a vertical direction of the IQ plane;
a minimum distance between signal points in one of the four groups and signal points in a rest of the four groups is a second distance which is different from the first distance;
the second symbol is arranged at a second position on the IQ plane where the first bit set in the plurality of bits is allocated; and
the second position and the first position are different.

5. A transmission method comprising:
a first symbol generation step of selecting one point of a first plurality of signal points as a first symbol, the first plurality of signal points being arranged per unit time on an IQ plane based on a first mapping pattern where a plurality of bits are allocated;
a second symbol generation step of selecting one point of a second plurality of signal points as a second symbol, the second plurality of signal points being arranged per unit time on the IQ plane based on a second mapping pattern where different bit allocation from the first mapping pattern is performed; and
a transmission step in which a first antenna transmits the first symbol and a second antenna transmits the second symbol in a common frequency and a common transmission time with the first symbol, wherein:
the first symbol is arranged at a first position on the IQ plane where a first bit set in the plurality of bits is allocated;
the first plurality of signal points are divided into four groups based on specific two bits of the plurality of bits;
in each of the groups, the first plurality of signal points are arranged per first distance in a horizontal direction or in a vertical direction of the IQ plane;
a minimum distance between signal points in one of the four groups and signal points in a rest of the four groups is a second distance which is different from the first distance;
the second symbol is arranged at a second position on the IQ plane where the first hit set in the plurality of bits is allocated; and
the second position and the first position are different.

6. A receiving apparatus comprising:
a plurality of antennas that receives a signal where a plurality of signals are multiplexed;
a channel estimation section that generates a channel estimation value using a predetermined signal included in the received signal; and
a signal processing section that separates the received signal using the channel estimation value, wherein:
the received signal includes (i) a first symbol that is one point selected from a first plurality of signal points arranged per unit time on an IQ plane based on a first mapping pattern where a plurality of bits are allocated, and (ii) a second symbol that is one point selected from a second plurality of signal points arranged per unit time on the IQ plane based on a second mapping pattern where different bit allocation from the first mapping pattern is performed;
the first symbol is arranged at a first position on the IQ plane where a first bit set in the plurality of bits is allocated;
the second symbol is arranged at a second position on the IQ plane where the first bit set in the plurality of bits is allocated;
the first position and the second position are different;
the first plurality of signal points are divided into four groups based on specific two bits in the plurality of bits;
in each of the groups, the first plurality of signal points are arranged per first distance in a horizontal direction or in a vertical direction of the IQ plane; and
a minimum distance between signal points in one of the four groups and signal points in a rest of the four groups is a second distance which is different from the first distance.

9. A receiving method comprising:
receiving a signal where a plurality of signals are multiplexed using a plurality of antennas;
generating a channel estimation value using a predetermined signal included in the received signal; and
separating the received signal using the channel estimation value, wherein:
the received signal includes (i) a first symbol that is one point selected from a first plurality of signal points arranged per unit time on an IQ plane based on a first mapping pattern where a plurality of bits are allocated, and (ii) a second symbol that is one point selected from a second plurality of signal points arranged per unit time on the IQ plane based on a second mapping pattern where different bit allocation from the first mapping pattern is performed;
the first symbol is arranged at a first position on the IQ plane where a first bit set is arranged among the plurality of bits;
the second symbol is arranged at a second position on the IQ plane where the first bit set in the plurality of bits is allocated;
the first position and the second position are different;
the first plurality of signal points are divided into four groups based on specific two bits in the plurality of bits;
in each of the groups, the first plurality of signal points are arranged per first distance in a horizontal direction or in a vertical direction of the IQ plane; and
a minimum distance between signal points in one of the four groups and signal points in a rest of the four groups is a second distance which is different from the first distance.
